\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Computational graph of the CLESSO neural network forward pass (transform-interaction beta variant; Section~\ref {sec:transform-interaction-beta}). \textbf  {Blue nodes}: alpha (richness) pathway --- per-site environmental covariates $\mathbf  {z}$ pass through a shared-weight AlphaNet (MLP) to produce $\alpha _i, \alpha _j > 1$ via softplus~$+$~1. \textbf  {Dashed nodes/arrows}: optional EffortNet pathway --- effort covariates $\mathbf  {w}$ produce a capture-completeness fraction $c \in (0,1)$ that modulates apparent richness (default: completeness mode, $\alpha ^{\mathrm  {obs}} = 1 + c\cdot \mathrm  {softplus}(\mathrm  {env\_logit})$). \textbf  {Green nodes}: beta (turnover) pathway --- per-site standardised environment vectors $\tilde  {\mathbf  {x}}_i, \tilde  {\mathbf  {x}}_j$ pass through shared-weight monotone transforms $T_k$, producing transformed separations $d^{(T)}_{k,ij} = |T_k(\tilde  {x}_{k,i}) - T_k(\tilde  {x}_{k,j})|$ (GDM I-spline analogue). \textbf  {Main path}: per-dimension origin-anchored weighting functions $g_k$ yield additive contributions $s_{k,ij} = g_k(d^{(T)}_{k,ij}) - g_k(0)$, summed to $z^{\mathrm  {main}}$. \textbf  {Interaction path}: shallow monotone encoders $e_k$ map each $d^{(T)}_{k,ij}$ to a low-dimensional embedding; the concatenated vector $\mathbf  {h}_{ij} \in \mathbb  {R}^{m d_{\mathrm  {enc}}}$ is passed through a monotone interaction network $\phi $ with baseline subtraction, yielding a cross-dimension correction $z^{\mathrm  {int}}_{ij} = \phi (\mathbf  {h}_{ij}) - \phi (\mathbf  {0})$, scaled by $\lambda _{\mathrm  {int}}$. The combined predictor $z^{\mathrm  {main}} + \lambda _{\mathrm  {int}}\,z^{\mathrm  {int}}$ is mapped through a sigmoid clamp ($\sigma _c$) to turnover $\eta \in (0, \eta _{\max })$ and similarity $S = e^{-\eta }$. \textbf  {Orange/red nodes}: likelihood and loss --- the match probability $p$ is computed from $\alpha _i, \alpha _j, S$, and $\texttt  {is\_within}$, corrected via the retrospective Bernoulli adjustment, and evaluated under per-stratum BCE with design weights. Penalty terms (lower-bound, anchor, anti-collapse, effort $L_2$) feed into the composite loss $\mathcal  {L}$. ``sp'' = softplus; ``$\sigma $'' = sigmoid; ``$\sigma _c$'' = sigmoid clamp $\eta _{\max }\cdot \sigma (\cdot - s)$; ``retro'' = retrospective Bernoulli correction.}}{3}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:comp-graph}{{1}{3}{Computational graph of the CLESSO neural network forward pass (transform-interaction beta variant; Section~\ref {sec:transform-interaction-beta}). \textbf {Blue nodes}: alpha (richness) pathway --- per-site environmental covariates $\mathbf {z}$ pass through a shared-weight AlphaNet (MLP) to produce $\alpha _i, \alpha _j > 1$ via softplus~$+$~1. \textbf {Dashed nodes/arrows}: optional EffortNet pathway --- effort covariates $\mathbf {w}$ produce a capture-completeness fraction $c \in (0,1)$ that modulates apparent richness (default: completeness mode, $\alpha ^{\mathrm {obs}} = 1 + c\cdot \mathrm {softplus}(\mathrm {env\_logit})$). \textbf {Green nodes}: beta (turnover) pathway --- per-site standardised environment vectors $\tilde {\mathbf {x}}_i, \tilde {\mathbf {x}}_j$ pass through shared-weight monotone transforms $T_k$, producing transformed separations $d^{(T)}_{k,ij} = |T_k(\tilde {x}_{k,i}) - T_k(\tilde {x}_{k,j})|$ (GDM I-spline analogue). \textbf {Main path}: per-dimension origin-anchored weighting functions $g_k$ yield additive contributions $s_{k,ij} = g_k(d^{(T)}_{k,ij}) - g_k(0)$, summed to $z^{\mathrm {main}}$. \textbf {Interaction path}: shallow monotone encoders $e_k$ map each $d^{(T)}_{k,ij}$ to a low-dimensional embedding; the concatenated vector $\mathbf {h}_{ij} \in \mathbb {R}^{m d_{\mathrm {enc}}}$ is passed through a monotone interaction network $\phi $ with baseline subtraction, yielding a cross-dimension correction $z^{\mathrm {int}}_{ij} = \phi (\mathbf {h}_{ij}) - \phi (\mathbf {0})$, scaled by $\lambda _{\mathrm {int}}$. The combined predictor $z^{\mathrm {main}} + \lambda _{\mathrm {int}}\,z^{\mathrm {int}}$ is mapped through a sigmoid clamp ($\sigma _c$) to turnover $\eta \in (0, \eta _{\max })$ and similarity $S = e^{-\eta }$. \textbf {Orange/red nodes}: likelihood and loss --- the match probability $p$ is computed from $\alpha _i, \alpha _j, S$, and $\texttt {is\_within}$, corrected via the retrospective Bernoulli adjustment, and evaluated under per-stratum BCE with design weights. Penalty terms (lower-bound, anchor, anti-collapse, effort $L_2$) feed into the composite loss $\mathcal {L}$. ``sp'' = softplus; ``$\sigma $'' = sigmoid; ``$\sigma _c$'' = sigmoid clamp $\eta _{\max }\cdot \sigma (\cdot - s)$; ``retro'' = retrospective Bernoulli correction}{figure.1}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Computational graph of the CLESSO neural network backward pass (gradient flow). \textbf  {Red/orange nodes}: gradient chain from the composite loss $\mathcal  {L}$ through the per-stratum BCE, retrospective Bernoulli correction, and log-space match probability to the three parameter groups. Solid red arrows show the primary gradient flow from $\mathcal  {L}_{\mathrm  {BCE}}$; dashed red arrows show penalty contributions ($\mathcal  {L}_{\mathrm  {lb}}$, $\mathcal  {L}_{\mathrm  {anch}}$, $\mathcal  {L}_{\mathrm  {AC}}$, etc.). \textbf  {Violet nodes}: gradient modifications --- $\times 100$ backward hook on BetaNet parameters (compensating $e^{-\eta }$ attenuation) and global gradient clipping ($\lVert \nabla \rVert _2 \leq 5$). \textbf  {Cyan nodes}: Adam optimisers with per-phase differential learning rates. The right panel summarises the cyclic block-coordinate training schedule: Phase~1A trains $\theta _\alpha $ on within-site pairs while freezing $\theta _\beta $; Phase~1B trains $\theta _\beta $ on between-site pairs while freezing $\theta _\alpha $; Phase~2 fine-tunes all parameters jointly with differential LR ($10\times $ higher for $\beta $); Phase~3 (optional) runs a short calibration pass. Key design property: the log-space formulation ensures $\partial \log p / \partial \eta = -1$ regardless of $\alpha $ magnitude, and the retrospective correction normalises match/mismatch gradient scales to $O(1)$.}}{5}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:backward-pass}{{2}{5}{Computational graph of the CLESSO neural network backward pass (gradient flow). \textbf {Red/orange nodes}: gradient chain from the composite loss $\mathcal {L}$ through the per-stratum BCE, retrospective Bernoulli correction, and log-space match probability to the three parameter groups. Solid red arrows show the primary gradient flow from $\mathcal {L}_{\mathrm {BCE}}$; dashed red arrows show penalty contributions ($\mathcal {L}_{\mathrm {lb}}$, $\mathcal {L}_{\mathrm {anch}}$, $\mathcal {L}_{\mathrm {AC}}$, etc.). \textbf {Violet nodes}: gradient modifications --- $\times 100$ backward hook on BetaNet parameters (compensating $e^{-\eta }$ attenuation) and global gradient clipping ($\lVert \nabla \rVert _2 \leq 5$). \textbf {Cyan nodes}: Adam optimisers with per-phase differential learning rates. The right panel summarises the cyclic block-coordinate training schedule: Phase~1A trains $\theta _\alpha $ on within-site pairs while freezing $\theta _\beta $; Phase~1B trains $\theta _\beta $ on between-site pairs while freezing $\theta _\alpha $; Phase~2 fine-tunes all parameters jointly with differential LR ($10\times $ higher for $\beta $); Phase~3 (optional) runs a short calibration pass. Key design property: the log-space formulation ensures $\partial \log p / \partial \eta = -1$ regardless of $\alpha $ magnitude, and the retrospective correction normalises match/mismatch gradient scales to $O(1)$}{figure.2}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Full pipeline computational graph from sample generation to spatial prediction. \textbf  {Grey}: raw input data (occurrence records, environmental and effort covariates, optional richness anchor raster). \textbf  {Orange}: R sampling pipeline --- \texttt  {obs\_pair\_sampler.R} generates hex-balanced match/mismatch pairs, \texttt  {clesso\_sampler} stratifies them into within-site (W) and three between-site distance tiers (S, N, D), and \texttt  {export\_for\_nn.R} writes the training artefacts. \textbf  {Yellow}: training artefacts loaded into Python --- \texttt  {pairs.feather} (observation pairs with targets and design weights) and \texttt  {metadata.json} (per-stratum retention rates and covariate names). \textbf  {Blue}: training loop --- \texttt  {run\_clesso\_nn.py} orchestrates cyclic block-coordinate descent through the CLESSONet model (single node; internal architecture shown in Figs.~\ref {fig:comp-graph} and~\ref {fig:backward-pass}); the best validation checkpoint is saved to disk (with an optional short calibration pass). \textbf  {Green}: spatial prediction --- \texttt  {predict\_alpha\_surface.py} runs a batched forward pass over all land cells ($0.05^\circ $ grid) to produce a species richness GeoTIFF; \texttt  {predict\_beta\_surface.py} selects landmark pixels, computes pairwise $\eta $, applies landmark MDS with Nystr\"{o}m extension, and writes an RGB turnover map and optional cluster GeoTIFF. Dashed arrows denote optional or secondary data flows (effort covariates, richness anchor, calibrated checkpoint).}}{6}{figure.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:full-pipeline}{{3}{6}{Full pipeline computational graph from sample generation to spatial prediction. \textbf {Grey}: raw input data (occurrence records, environmental and effort covariates, optional richness anchor raster). \textbf {Orange}: R sampling pipeline --- \texttt {obs\_pair\_sampler.R} generates hex-balanced match/mismatch pairs, \texttt {clesso\_sampler} stratifies them into within-site (W) and three between-site distance tiers (S, N, D), and \texttt {export\_for\_nn.R} writes the training artefacts. \textbf {Yellow}: training artefacts loaded into Python --- \texttt {pairs.feather} (observation pairs with targets and design weights) and \texttt {metadata.json} (per-stratum retention rates and covariate names). \textbf {Blue}: training loop --- \texttt {run\_clesso\_nn.py} orchestrates cyclic block-coordinate descent through the CLESSONet model (single node; internal architecture shown in Figs.~\ref {fig:comp-graph} and~\ref {fig:backward-pass}); the best validation checkpoint is saved to disk (with an optional short calibration pass). \textbf {Green}: spatial prediction --- \texttt {predict\_alpha\_surface.py} runs a batched forward pass over all land cells ($0.05^\circ $ grid) to produce a species richness GeoTIFF; \texttt {predict\_beta\_surface.py} selects landmark pixels, computes pairwise $\eta $, applies landmark MDS with Nystr\"{o}m extension, and writes an RGB turnover map and optional cluster GeoTIFF. Dashed arrows denote optional or secondary data flows (effort covariates, richness anchor, calibrated checkpoint)}{figure.3}{}}
